Male
– Head horn (
Fig. 227
) erect, plate-like, set very near eyes; width approaching interocular distance, sides more-or-less parallel; apex tridentate, emarginations separating teeth deep, rounded. Pronotal prominence (
Fig. 247
) strongly bilobate, lobes directed anteriorly and flanked by shallow concavities; width of prominence clearly less than distance between outer margins of eyes. Apical processes of parameres tooth-like.
